===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|p}} – the sun. A dot or line was added in the centre to distinguish it from visually similar characters, e.g. {{l|zh|口}}. Compare earlier forms of the character with the astronomical and astrological symbol for the Sun ([[☉]]) and the Egyptian hieroglyph {{m|egy|𓇳}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=囸-ancient,𡆠,𡇁,𡆸-ancient,𡇗,𡈎,𲘞}}

From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ku-ni(k)}}. Cognate to {{cog|bo|ཉི་མ||tr=nyi ma|sun, day}}, {{cog|my|နေ||tr=ne|sun}} or {{cog|my|နေ့||tr=ne.|day}}, {{cog|ksw|နံၤ||tr=nĩ|day}}, and {{cog|ii|ꑍ||tr=nyip|day, daytime}}.

